Javascript: Regular Expressions

RegExp.test(string) -> returns TRUE or FALSE
string.match(string/regular expression) -> returns match

To match multiple values: Use OR or |

Flags
Ignore Upper/Lower Cases: /___/i
Find multiple instances of match(find more than the first match): /___/g
Wildcard: /___./ -> matches any one character 
Match repeating Characters (1 or more): /__+/
Match repeating Characters (0 or more): /__*/
Lazy matching: /___?/
Match beginning: /^___/
Match ending: /___$/
Check for all or none: /__x?_/

Character Classes /__[__]__/ -> Allow you to define a group of characters to match.
Alphabet: [a-z]
Alphabet & Numbers: [a-z0-9]
Negated Character Set: /[^___]/ -> Character you don’t want to match

Short Hand Character Classes
/\w/: [A-Za-z0-9_]
/\W/: [^A-Za-z0-9_]
/\d/: [0-9]
/\D/: [^0-9]
/\s/: Whitespace [\r\t\f\n\v]
/\S/: [^\r\t\f\n\v]

Quantity Specifiers {_,_}
Lower/Upper number: {_,}/{,_}
Exact: {_}

Lookahead 
Positive lookahead:(?=…) where … is the required part that is not matched
Negative lookahead:(?!…) where … is the pattern you do not want to be there

Capture Groups: ( )




